{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀποκατά-στᾰσις</b>, εως, ἡ, <br /> <b>restoration, re-establishment,</b> τοῦ ἐνδεοῦς[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Magna Moralia” 1205a4; εἰς φύσιν [prev. work] 1204b36, 1205b11\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>return to</b> a position, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Epistulae” 1p.8U.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; especially of military formations, <b>reversal</b> of a movement, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Asclepiodotus Tacticus “Tact.” 10.6, etc.; generally, πάντων NT.Act.3.21 \">NT+1st c.BC+</a>]; of the soul, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD: Proclus Philosophus “Inst.” 199 (_plural_); τῆς φύσιος ἐς τὸ ἀρχαῖον 2nd c.AD: Aretaeus Medicus “χρονίων νούσων θεραπευτικόν” 1.5\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; <b>recovery from sickness,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “SA” 1.10; τῶν ὁμήρων εἰς τὰς πατρίδας 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 3.99.6\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; εἰς ἀ. ἐλθεῖν, of the affairs of a city, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 4.23.1\">Refs</a>]; <b>return</b> to original position, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Asclepiodotus Tacticus “Tact.” 10.1\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; ἀ. ἄστρων <b>return</b> of the stars to the same place in the heavens as in the former year, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.937f, 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 12.36, etc.\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; <b>periodic return</b> of the cosmic cycle, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Stoicorum Veterum Fragmenta” 2.184,190 \">Refs</a>]; of a planet, <b>return</b> to a place in the heavens occupied at a former epoch, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Antiochus Atheniensis Astrologus cited in “Catalogus Codicum Astrologorum” 7.120,121\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; but, <b>zodiacal revolution,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Paulus Alexandrinus Astrologus “T.” 1\">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]; opposed to ἀνταπ. (which see), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Dorotheus Astrologus cited in “Catalogus Codicum Astrologorum” 2.196.9\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; <b>restoration</b> of sun and moon after eclipse, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Axiochus” 370b.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0605","accentedUnicode":"ἀποκατάστασις","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0575","matchingForm":"ἀπό","stepTransliteration":"apo","gloss":"away from","_zh_tw_Gloss":"從","_es_Gloss":"de","_zh_Gloss":"从"},{"strongNumber":"G0600","matchingForm":"ἀποκαθίστημι","stepTransliteration":"apokathistēmi","gloss":"to restore","_zh_tw_Gloss":"復了原","_es_Gloss":"restaurar","_zh_Gloss":"复了原"},{"strongNumber":"G0604","matchingForm":"ἀποκαταλλάσσω","stepTransliteration":"apokatallassō","gloss":"to reconcile","_zh_tw_Gloss":"好了","_es_Gloss":"reconciliar","_zh_Gloss":"好了"},{"strongNumber":"G2525","matchingForm":"καθίστημι","stepTransliteration":"kathistēmi","gloss":"to appoint/conduct","_zh_tw_Gloss":"要派, 成為, 立","_es_Gloss":"asignar/conducir","_zh_Gloss":"要派, 成为, 立"}],"shortDef":"restoration","mediumDef":"<i>primarily</i> <b>a restitution</b> or <b>restoration of</b> a thing to its former state; hence, <b>the renovation</b> of a new and better era, <ref='Act.3.21'>Acts 3:21</ref>*","stepGloss":"restoration","stepTransliteration":"apokatastasis","count":1,"_es_Definition":"restauración, renovación","_zh_tw_Definition":"恢復 (徒 3:21)","_zh_Definition":"恢复 (徒 3:21)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"sự phục hồi; tái lập, tái thiết, tái xây dựng","_zh_tw_Gloss":"復興","_es_Gloss":"restauración","_zh_Gloss":"复兴"}]}